      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>Camera Projections are the lens through which RenderMan views the digital scene.  You can create custom projection plugins using C++.  RenderMan comes with multiple plugins with PxrCamera being the common projection. The Omnidirectional Stereo projection renders images in a format suitable for VR viewing.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"8b0a773d-4b02-4e69-9cd8-57f3bffb989a\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>See <a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661781\" rel=\"nofollow\">Projection Plugins</a> for more information.</p></div></div><p /><h3 id=\"CameraProjections-CustomCameraProjection\">Custom Camera Projection</h3><p>In your RIS Network, create a <a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661243\" rel=\"nofollow\">PxrCamera</a> VOP.</p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"319\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644832/pxrcamera.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=319&amp;height=391\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644832/pxrcamera.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"432\" data-width=\"352\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644851\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"pxrcamera.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644832\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e226c25c-2106-4715-8893-1b56254c4fe8\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644832/pxrcamera.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=352&amp;height=432 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644832/pxrcamera.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=319&amp;height=391 1x\"></span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"1ece239f-02c9-4d83-bf00-9daf5a4ed8ae\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Only one custom projection plugin can be added to the camera.</p></div></div><p>To use the custom camera projection, select &quot;Lens Shader&quot; in the camera View tab. Now, in the RenderMan tab (created with the &quot;Add Spare Params&quot; shelf icon) connect the PxrProjection, like PxrCamera, to the Lens Shader connection in the Tab as seen below. Drag the camera projection VOP to the Lens Shader parameter.</p><p>The Lens Shader parameter on the camera you activate is meant for Mantra so we use a different connection allowing you to move back and forth between them.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"646\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644832/camlensshader.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=646&amp;height=243\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644832/camlensshader.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"326\" data-width=\"865\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644854\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"camlensshader.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644832\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"13d6e6d6-60fd-4f5d-a466-aabd2b3d53bc\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644832/camlensshader.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=865&amp;height=326 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644832/camlensshader.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433133062&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=646&amp;height=243 1x\"></span><p />"
    }
